description.en-US: Cascading Style Sheets allow us to to serve a better and prettier user experience. I am a fan of preprocessors such as SASS and LESS as they allow for reusable variables and mixins, giving any site a more consistent feel.

The barebones for any website, well written semantic HTML is important and allows for better accessiblity to all users. I pick HTML elements based on their semantic meaning rather than visual presentation.

Javascript is fundamental for single page applications and dynamic components. MVC design patterns in the past helped us achieve this, and with newer frameworks like React, it is easier than ever to create dynamic functioning websites.

I am a front-end developer who is passionate for creating modern & functional web applications that have a clean and intuitive user interface. I love writing modular code that is re-usable and integrating internal/external data from RESTful API's and GraphQL into my work. I have experience in front-end frameworks such as React and Angular, libraries like jQuery and Lodash, as well as back-end
Node frameworks like Express. I enjoy working on teams with clear and constant communication techniques that allow for better organization. My experience creating applications demonstrates my ability to create a rich user experience for the client.
